    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (excerpt excerption selection)
  entry
    definition "remove, usually with some force or effort; also used in an abstract sense"
    examples ("pull weeds" "extract a bad tooth" "take out a splinter" "extract information from the telegram")
    id oewn-01353852-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms ("pull out" pull "pull up" "take out" "draw out" "rip out" "tear out")
  entry
    definition "get despite difficulties or obstacles"
    examples ("I extracted a promise from the Dean for two new positions")
    id oewn-02243880-v
    partOfSpeech v
  entry
    definition "deduce (a principle) or construe (a meaning)"
    examples ("We drew out some interesting linguistic data from the native informant")
    id oewn-01634074-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (educe evoke elicit "draw out")
  entry
    definition "extract by the process of distillation"
    examples ("distill the essence of this compound")
    id oewn-00229706-v
    partOfSpeech v
    synonyms (distill distil)
  entry
    definition "separate (a metal) from an ore"
    id oewn-01462021-v
    partOfSpeech v
  entry
    definition "obtain from a substance, as by mechanical action"
    examples ("Italians express coffee rather than filter it")
